---
import BaseLayout from "../../components/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import DownloadTiles from "../../components/fragments/DownloadTiles.astro";
import Main from "../../components/Main.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Musicopy | Manual">
  <Nav />

  <Main>
    <h1>Manual</h1>

    <h2>1. Install both apps</h2>

    <DownloadTiles />

    <h2>2. Add your music</h2>

    <div class="clearfix">
      <img src="/static/manual/desktop_home.png" class="right" />

      <p>In the desktop app, add folders to your library.</p>

      <p>
        Added folders will be scanned and their contents will be available for
        download in the mobile app.
      </p>

      <p>
        Musicopy can automatically convert files to improve file size or
        compatibility, or transfer the original files. You can change this
        setting in the mobile app. <a href="/manual/transcoding"
          >More information</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Connect your phone</h2>

    <div class="clearfix">
      <img src="/static/manual/mobile_home.png" class="left" />

      <p>
        In the mobile app, scan the QR code shown in the desktop app to connect.
      </p>

      <p>
        After clicking accept, Musicopy will create a direct end-to-end
        encrypted connection for fast and private transfers. Both devices can
        even be on different networks.
      </p>

      <p>
        Next time, Musicopy will list recent connections to reconnect quickly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>4. Transfer your files</h2>

    <div class="clearfix">
      <img src="/static/manual/mobile_transfer.png" class="right" />
      <img src="/static/manual/mobile_pretransfer.png" class="right" />

      <p>Choose files from your library and start the transfer.</p>

      <p>
        Downloaded files will be saved to your chosen folder, mirroring your
        folder structure on desktop.
      </p>

      <p>
        Next time, Musicopy will remember which files have already been
        transferred.
      </p>

      <p>
        On Android, transfers continue in the background. On iOS, keep the app
        open until the transfer finishes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>More information</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/manual/transcoding">Transcoding</a></li>
    </ul>
  </Main>

  <div class="flex-1"></div>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  img {
    background-color: var(--color-secondary-container);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
  }

  .left {
    float: left;
    max-height: 300px;
    margin-right: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .right {
    float: right;
    max-height: 300px;
    margin-left: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  @media screen and (max-width: 800px) {
    .left,
    .right {
      width: 50%;
    }
  }

  .clearfix::after {
    content: "";
    clear: both;
    display: table;
  }
</style>
